f \in C^1(\mathbb{R^2})
f_n(x,y) = \int_{\mathbb{T}} f(k(\theta)(x,y))e^{-2\pi i n\theta}\mathrm{d}\theta
k(\theta) = \begin{pmatrix} \cos \theta & -\sin\theta \\ \sin\theta & \cos \theta \\ \end{pmatrix}
\mathbb{T} = \mathbb{R}/\mathbb{Z}
f(x,y) = \sum_{n\in\mathbb{Z}} f_n(x,y)
f \in L^2(\mathbb{R^2})
L^2
